ulated (NORMAL, ALWAYS, FORCED, ONREFMOVE, etc.). When a cell's precedents (dependencies) change, the `ScDocument` class (in sc/source/core/data/document.cxx) broadcasts notifications that trigger dirty-marking of dependent cells via the ScFormulaCell::SetDirty() method. The document maintains recalculation state and controls the overall recalculation cycle through methods like DoRecalc() and DoHardRecalc().\n\nThe complete evaluation chain: Formula String → ScCompiler (tokenization) → ScFormulaCell (storage & dirty tracking) → ScInterpreter (bytecode evaluation) → Result cached in ScFormulaCell, with dependency tracking managed by ScDocument's recalculation system."
